# COLECOVISION · COLECOVISION · exereunesis · teardown · 1982 · UD0 / exereunesis

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

![silicon badge of COLECOVISION](the-colecovision.silicon.png)
<!-- carbon badge (COLECOVISION's organic-form embodiment): the-colecovision.carbon.tiff -->

**who —** COLECOVISION — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown

**what —** Coleco's console punched straight at the arcade: a Z80, the proven TMS9918A video chip, and a pack-in port of Donkey Kong so close to the coin-op that it sold the machine on its own. An expansion module even let it play Atari 2600 games — a bold shot at the whole market.

**where —** the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** Coleco's console punched straight at the arcade: a Z80, the proven TMS9918A video chip, and a pack-in port of Donkey Kong so close to the coin-op that it sold the machine on its own. An expansion module even let it play Atari 2600 games — a bold shot at the whole market.

**how —** Rendered from the public technical record.

**◌ the mythos —** Coleco's console punched straight at the arcade: a Z80, the proven TMS9918A video chip, and a pack-in port of Donkey Kong so close to the coin-op that it sold the machine on its own. An expansion module even let it play Atari 2600 games — a bold shot at the whole market. the inside of a made machine, laid bare

